<item>
            <title>[LU-8405] MGT should check servicenode nid before accepting mount</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8405</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The MGS will just accept a mount request even if the servicenode arguments are invalid nids. This results in the OST going to &quot;partial connect: state when the MDT tried to use the bad nids and also the mount being put into the replay log, so that the partial attach never goes away. It survives a reboot, lustre_rmmod and remount of the MGT and MDT.It gets replayed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The MGS should check all the failover nids (even a simple lctl ping) before accepting the mount, Allowing it to be accepted causes too many problems downstream.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="38200">LU-8405</key>
