                            <comment id="160288" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Fri, 29 Jul 2016 11:08:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the problem here is target will register itself without any nid in &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;mti-&amp;gt;mti_nids (struct mgs_target_info) &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; if the &quot;--servicenode&quot; param is given&lt;br/&gt;
the incorrect nodes, and the MGS will use the first nid in mti-&amp;gt;mti_nids (will be zero!) to create the config log entry of &quot;setup&quot;, which cause this problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/19933/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/19933/&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8091&quot; title=&quot;server_lsi2mti() should return error when fail to get nid&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8091&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8091&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; can fix the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
